               <p>A native of <placeName>Watford, Wales</placeName>, Price was a prominent supporter
                  of the evangelical revival in <placeName>Wales</placeName>. While his sympathies,
                  like most Methodists in <placeName>Wales</placeName>, leaned to Calvinism, Price
                  welcomed the Wesley brothers to his home and accompanied them on their early
                  preaching missions in <placeName>Wales</placeName>.</p>
